<EclipsedMoon99> Temperatures in the interior of the Earth are so high that the rock would melt if the pressure were not so great. Radioactive atoms break up at a slow rate, keeping the temperatures high. Some mantle rock partially melts (only some minerals melt) and forces its way up to the surface. The minerals in the mantle that melt are the silicon compounds that make up the Earth's crust.
<EclipsedMoon99> The density of rocks near the surface of the Earth is only about 3 times that of water, so the interior must be made of much heavier materials such as iron and nickel. The Earth's magnetic field shows that the core can hold or cause a strong magnetic field. Iron is the logical material, because of its high density and its magnetic properties.

<Hawkie> 07May, here's my plotline idea for the competiton. I never got to write it though
<Hawkie> 07So might as well just say it.
<Hawkie> 07Since it was a love-story, I assumed that Lugia and Articuno would get married at one point -- with Lugia wanting to porpose to her under the mistletoe (to involve the theme, y'know?) -- but they'd have to find it. Seems fine so far... Right.
<Hawkie> 07
<Hawkie> 07I would've revealed this in the story if I'd ever gotten that far -- Ho-oh somehow getting the bright idea that he wanted Articuno for himself. After all, Lugia was less of a bird than he was, although he'd have done his fair share of bribery and convincing to get Lugia to agree to this... Giving up Arti and letting him have her, that is.
<Hawkie> 07And to cover it up, Lugia had Zapdos and Moltres make this stew thing that they would apply to the leaves of the mistletoe, which of course, again, to include the theme, could only be found in one place. That way, Lugia would look innocent.
<Hawkie> 07
<Hawkie> 07When Lugia and Articuno went to find the mistletoe, she wouldn't suspect much, with Lugia encouraging her to pick it up -- and she'd have to do this with her beak, as there's really no other effective way of plucking a plant for a bird.
<Kyogre> 03too much oranga @_@
<Kyogre> 03orange
<Hawkie> 07This way, it would be unavoidable for her to lap up some of the substance applied to it earlier, resulting in her losing grasp of reality for a bit... Which is where Ho-oh would've entered the picture, claimed Arti, still with the mistletoe in her beak, and that would be that.
